Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic Properties of Mixtures Containing Ionic Liquids.4.LLE of Binary Mixtures of [C2MIM][NTf2] with Propan-1-ol, Butan-1-ol, and Pentan-1-ol and [C4MIM][NTf2] with Cyclohexanol and 1,2-Hexanediol Including Studies of the Influence of Small Amounts of Water
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental data are presented for liquid-liquid equilibria of mixtures of the room-temperature ionic liquid 1-ethyl-3-methyl-imidazolium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)imide ([C2MIM][NTf2]) with the three alcohols propan-1-ol, butan-1-ol, and pentan-1-ol and for the 1-butyl-3-methyl-imidazolium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl) imide ([C4MIM][NTf2]) with cyclohexanol and 1,2-hexanediol in the temperature range of 275 K to 345 K at ambient pressure. The synthetic method has been used. Cloud points at a given composition were observed by varying the temperature and using light scattering to detect the phase splitting. In addition, the influence of small amounts of water on the demixing temperatures of binary mixtures of [C2MIM][NTf2] and propan-1-ol, butan-1-ol, and pentan-1-ol was investigated.
